## 4. Functional requirements

### 4.1 Authentication & user management (Priority: CRITICAL)

- User registration with email verification
- JWT-based authentication with 15-minute access token + 7-day refresh token
- Two-factor authentication (2FA) for account security
- Password reset via email
- User profile management (name, email, trading style preference)
- Subscription tier management (free → pro → enterprise)
- API key generation for power users (Pro tier only)

### 4.2 Broker account connection (Priority: CRITICAL)

- Connect Angel One Smart API with encrypted credentials storage
- Connect Zerodha Kite API with encrypted credentials storage
- Secure OAuth/API key management (never logged in plaintext)
- Account info display (portfolio value, available cash, margin)
- Multi-broker support (same user can connect 2+ brokers)
- Disconnect broker without data loss

### 4.3 Strategy management (Priority: CRITICAL)

- Create strategies with no-code UI (drag-drop conditions)
- Define strategy parameters: entry/exit rules, timeframe (1min to daily)
- Support 3 initial strategy types:
  - **EMA Crossover**: Buy when EMA5 crosses above EMA20, sell on crossover down
  - **RSI Momentum**: Buy when RSI < 30 (oversold), sell when RSI > 70
  - **Breakout**: Buy when price breaks above 52-week high, sell on pullback
- Clone existing strategies for iteration
- Edit strategy parameters (safe: no running trades affected)
- Pause/resume strategies (stop new signals, keep open trades)
- Delete strategies (only if no active trades)
- Export strategy as JSON for sharing

### 4.4 Backtesting engine (Priority: CRITICAL)

- Run historical simulation on 1-10 years of data
- Support multiple timeframes (1min, 5min, 15min, 1hr, daily)
- Calculate professional metrics:
  - Win rate (% of profitable trades)
  - Profit factor (total profit / total loss, target > 1.5)
  - Sharpe ratio (risk-adjusted return)
  - Max drawdown (peak-to-trough decline)
  - Sortino ratio (downside-adjusted return)
  - Average trade duration
  - Largest win/loss
- Generate equity curve visualization (chart)
- Show trade-by-trade list with entry/exit prices
- Support different slippage assumptions (0%, 0.5%, 1%)
- Async job processing (backtest runs in background)
- Report completion via email + in-app notification
- Export backtest results as PDF/CSV

### 4.5 Live trading execution (Priority: CRITICAL)

- Deploy strategy to live trading (enable signal generation)
- Automatic order placement when signals triggered
- Market orders only (MVP Phase 1)
- Automatic SL/TP placement (atomic with entry order)
- Position tracking in real-time
- Manual position override (close early, modify SL/TP)
- Order status monitoring (pending, executed, failed)
- Trade confirmation logging (audit trail)
- Reconciliation with broker (hourly sync to verify trades match)

### 4.6 Risk management engine (Priority: HIGH)

- Position sizing calculation (fixed size or Kelly criterion)
- Stop-loss enforcement (required, can't place order without SL)
- Take-profit enforcement (optional, but recommended)
- Daily loss limit (pause all strategies if daily loss > limit %)
- Max open positions (e.g., max 5 stocks at once)
- Account leverage limit (never allow > 3x leverage)
- Real-time position P&L calculation
- Risk alerts (alert when positions near risk limit)

### 4.7 Portfolio analytics (Priority: HIGH)

- Dashboard overview (total value, today's P&L, monthly P&L)
- Per-strategy performance (win rate, Sharpe, monthly P&L)
- Sector allocation breakdown (% by sector)
- Individual trade history with filters (date, symbol, strategy)
- Performance comparison (backtest vs live results)
- Equity curve chart (portfolio value over time)
- Export analytics as PDF/CSV

### 4.8 Notifications & alerts (Priority: MEDIUM)

- Real-time trade execution alerts (email + in-app + push)
- SL/TP hit alerts
- Risk threshold breach alerts (daily loss limit reached)
- Backtest completion notification
- In-app notification center with history
- Email digest (daily/weekly summary of trades)
- Push notifications (optional, requires browser permission)

### 4.9 Strategy marketplace (Priority: MEDIUM, Phase 2)

- Share strategies publicly (opt-in)
- Strategy discovery page (browse community strategies)
- Strategy performance leaderboard (ranked by win rate, Sharpe)
- Revenue share (20% to creator, 80% to platform)
- Rating/review system (traders rate shared strategies)
- Strategy metadata (description, timeframe, risk profile)

### 4.10 Data management (Priority: HIGH)

- Historical OHLC data for 500+ NSE/BSE stocks
- Daily data refresh at 4:30 PM IST (after market close)
- Intraday data update every 5 minutes during market hours
- Support multiple timeframes (1min, 5min, 15min, 1hr, daily)
- Data quality validation (check for missing/outlier data)
- Data retention: 10 years minimum

### 4.11 Admin & monitoring (Priority: MEDIUM)

- Admin dashboard (user count, trades executed, system health)
- Error logging and monitoring (Sentry integration)
- Performance metrics (API latency, database queries)
- User management (view users, suspend accounts, refund)
- Revenue tracking (MRR, conversion rate, churn)

