## 8. Technical considerations

### 8.1 Integration points

- **Angel One Smart API**: OAuth/API key authentication, order placement, position sync, account info
- **Zerodha Kite API**: API key authentication, order placement, position sync, historical data
- **MetaTrader5 (MT5)**: Windows VPS running MT5 terminal, Python package communicates via REST API wrapper
- **Data providers**: NSE/BSE APIs for OHLC data, fallback to Alpha Vantage (rate-limited)
- **Payment gateway**: Stripe or Razorpay for subscription billing
- **Email service**: SendGrid for transactional emails (registration, password reset, trade alerts)
- **Push notifications**: Firebase Cloud Messaging for mobile/web push
- **Monitoring**: Sentry for error tracking, DataDog for performance monitoring

### 8.2 Data storage & privacy

- **Database**: PostgreSQL with TimescaleDB for time-series data (market data, position snapshots)
- **Encryption**: AES-256 for broker credentials at rest, TLS 1.3 for transit
- **Backup strategy**: Daily automated backups to S3, 3-copy redundancy, 3-year retention for trades
- **Data retention**: Keep user trades forever (immutable audit trail), market data for 10 years
- **GDPR/Privacy**: User data deletion on request, no third-party data sharing, clear privacy policy
- **Compliance**: Audit logs for all trades, comply with Indian tax regulations

### 8.3 Scalability & performance

- **API load**: Horizontal scaling with multiple Python FastAPI instances behind load balancer
- **Database**: Connection pooling (PgBouncer), read replicas for analytics queries
- **Caching**: Redis cluster for session tokens, strategy data, real-time prices
- **Async jobs**: Celery for background backtests, data refresh, reconciliation
- **CDN**: CloudFront for static assets (Next.js build)
- **Database sharding**: By user_id when > 10K users (future consideration)

### 8.4 Potential challenges

- **Broker API changes**: Each broker changes API frequently, requires versioning and monitoring
- **MT5 reliability**: Windows VPS can crash, requires monitoring and auto-restart
- **Backtesting accuracy**: Must ensure historical data is correct, slippage realistic, commissions accounted
- **Order execution timing**: Network delays and broker queues can affect execution price
- **Real money risk**: Traders can lose money, requires strong disclaimers and risk management
- **Regulatory uncertainty**: India crypto regulations changing, trading laws evolving
- **Competition**: Streak has brand recognition, must differentiate quickly
- **Data quality**: Historical data gaps for illiquid stocks, requires validation

