## 10. User stories

### 10.1 User registration and email verification

- **ID**: ATAP-001
- **Description**: As a new trader, I want to register with my email and password so that I can create an account and start using the platform.
- **Acceptance criteria**:
  - User can enter email, password (min 8 chars, 1 uppercase, 1 number)
  - Email verification link sent immediately
  - User confirms email by clicking link (expires in 24h)
  - Account created in free tier after verification
  - Welcome email with onboarding guide sent
  - User redirected to broker connection page after registration
  - Error: Email already exists → show message, suggest login

### 10.2 User login with JWT authentication

- **ID**: ATAP-002
- **Description**: As a registered trader, I want to log in with email/password so that I can access my account.
- **Acceptance criteria**:
  - User enters email and password
  - System validates credentials against hashed password in DB
  - JWT token generated (15-min expiry)
  - Refresh token generated (7-day expiry, stored as httpOnly cookie)
  - Redirect to dashboard
  - "Remember me" checkbox extends refresh token to 30 days
  - Invalid credentials → show error message, no account enumeration
  - Account locked after 5 failed attempts (15-min timeout)

### 10.3 Two-factor authentication (2FA) setup

- **ID**: ATAP-003
- **Description**: As a Pro user, I want to enable 2FA to protect my account from unauthorized access.
- **Acceptance criteria**:
  - User navigates to Settings → Security
  - System generates TOTP secret, shows QR code
  - User scans QR code with authenticator app (Google Authenticator, Authy)
  - User enters 6-digit code from authenticator
  - 2FA enabled, backup codes generated and shown
  - On next login, prompt for 2FA code
  - 2FA code invalid 3x → lock for 15 mins
  - Can disable 2FA with password confirmation

### 10.4 Connect Angel One broker account

- **ID**: ATAP-004
- **Description**: As a day trader with Angel One account, I want to connect my API credentials so that I can execute trades automatically.
- **Acceptance criteria**:
  - User clicks "Connect Broker" button
  - Modal shows Angel One setup steps
  - User enters: API Key, Client ID, TOTP secret
  - System validates credentials by making test API call to Angel One
  - If valid: Save encrypted credentials, mark account as "connected"
  - If invalid: Show error message with troubleshooting steps
  - Display account info: Portfolio value, available cash, margin
  - User can disconnect anytime (credentials deleted securely)
  - Broker session remains active across multiple trades

### 10.5 Connect Zerodha Kite broker account

